100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On December 21, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, addressing the growing tensions in Europe as nations grappled with post-World War I recovery. In the United States, a major winter storm disrupted transportation and commerce, leaving many cities in chaos. Meanwhile, the trial of John Scopes, known as the "Monkey Trial," continued to draw national attention, igniting fierce debates over science and religion in American classrooms.
